<div class="bs-docs-section">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>InputMirror <small>Delegator.InputMirror.js</small></h1>
  </div>
  <p>Delegator for tying the values of two inputs together. Note that this is not bi-directional. Changing the source
    input will update the target(s), but not vice versa. If you want that two-way mirror, put the trigger on each input.</p>

  <h3>Example</h3>
  <%= render layout: "codeblock" do %>
<div class="col">
  <div class="form-group col-md-3">
    <input type="text" class="form-control"
      data-trigger="inputMirror"
      data-inputmirror-targets="
      [
        {
          'selector': '!.col .target'
        }
      ]"
    />
  </div>
  <div class="form-group col-md-3">
    <input type="text" class="form-control target"/>
  </div>
</div>
  <% end %>
  <h2>Delegator Options</h2>
  <p>These options apply only to the <code>data-</code> tag invocation.</p>
  <div class="table-responsive">
    <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
      <thead>
       <tr>
         <th style="width: 100px;">Name</th>
         <th style="width: 50px;">type</th>
         <th style="width: 50px;">default</th>
         <th>description</th>
       </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>targets</td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>~</td>
          <td>Selector to find the mirrored input(s).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>property</td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>'value'</td>
          <td>The property to mirror.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
